---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is AT a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)"
  description="AT is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. A preposition meaning near or by. Extensions: ATE, ATS. Free word checker."
  keywords="is at a scrabble word, at scrabble, at valid scrabble, at points scrabble, two letter words scrabble, at meaning scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is AT a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)",
    "description": "AT is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. A preposition meaning near or by.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-at-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is AT a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, AT is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. It scores 2 points (A=1, T=1) and is a preposition meaning near, by, or in the position of." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What words can you extend AT into?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "AT extends into ATE, ATS, BAT, CAT, FAT, HAT, MAT, PAT, RAT, SAT, VAT. Front-hooks are especially powerful for parallel scoring." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is AT useful in competitive Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Absolutely. AT is one of the most versatile 2-letter words because both A and T are common tiles (9 A-tiles and 6 T-tiles). It hooks with nearly every consonant." } }
    ]
  })} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is AT a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>3 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, AT is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. AT is a preposition meaning near, by, or in the position of. While it only scores 2 base points, its real power is in its incredible hook versatility — nearly every consonant creates a valid 3-letter word when placed before AT.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ Valid Both</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">AT</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">2 points · A=1, T=1 · A preposition meaning near or by</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">AT is one of the most hookable 2-letter words in Scrabble. With 9 A-tiles and 6 T-tiles in the bag, you'll play AT frequently. Its true value lies in creating parallel plays and extending into dozens of 3-letter words.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">9 A-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">6 T-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AT Extensions</h2>
      <p>AT hooks with almost every consonant as a front-hook:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ATE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ATS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BAT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CAT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FAT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HAT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VAT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy with AT</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel play power:</span> Place AT parallel to an existing word to score on both. AT alongside a row of tiles triggers multiple crossword scores simultaneously.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square targeting:</span> AT on a DWS = 4 points. On a TWS = 6. Add crosswords and even this humble 2-pointer delivers double-digit turns.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup for hooks:</span> Play AT early near a DLS/TLS, then hook it with a high-value consonant (like VAT or HAT) next turn for combo scoring.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AT has more valid front-hooks than almost any other 2-letter word: <span class="text-white font-medium">BAT, CAT, FAT, GAT, HAT, KAT, LAT, MAT, OAT, PAT, RAT, SAT, TAT, VAT</span> — that's 14+ extensions from one tiny word.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ta-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is TA a Scrabble Word? Yes!</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-to-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is TO a Scrabble Word? Yes!</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
